# Documentation Sync Rules

## Core Principles

- Code, tests, README, and SDD documents must evolve together.
- Documentation is not a release-afterthought manual. It is part of the implementation constraints before and after coding.

## Sync Requirements

- Requirement changes: update `docs/workflow/01-requirements/README.md`
- Design changes: update `docs/workflow/02-design/README.md`
- Long-lived business or structural changes: update `docs/knowledge/`
- Delivery-order changes: update `docs/workflow/03-implementation/README.md`
- Testing-strategy changes: update `docs/workflow/04-verification/README.md`
- Task-breakdown changes: update `docs/workflow/05-tasks/README.md`
- Requirement, bug-fix, or refactor changes: update `docs/changes/active/` or the correct archive location
- Release changes: update `docs/releases/`
- Project-structure changes: update `README.md` and any affected rule docs

## Review Questions

- Does this code change still trace back to the intended `FR -> DES -> TEST -> T` chain?
- Did this work introduce new `[To confirm]` items that still need to be documented?
- Are any new rules only living in chat or PR comments instead of `docs/rules/`?
- Did this work update workflow but forget the corresponding knowledge or change workspace?
